      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "Star Kiwi MARKETPLACE NZ (2) looks well placed to atone for a defeat as favourite in his Australian debut when he drew the widest barrier at Menangle and worked but stuck on for a 3.3m third. That was his first outing for five weeks so it should have improved him and he races well over this shorter distance. The good draw gives him every chance to show what he can do. SEASIDER (1) has claimed some good scalps in winning both the Riverina and TAB Regional Championship finals this time in. He was just behind Marketplace when fourth in Sydney last start and the inside draw could see him make a race of it. CHEERSTOLOU (9) draws on the back row but he is a two-time second-up winner so should be improved and has a phenomenal record at this circuit and distance, winning 10 of 11 attempts. KANENA PROVLIMA (8) draws for a trail. That could see him competitive.",
